Mobiles.LongDescription: A scorpion with a fat red tail scuttles by you.
A brown scorpion with a long blue tail wanders here.
An oddly-colored sidewinder makes tracks in the sand here.
A scruffy desert rat roots around here, looking for food.
A sand-worm bursts out from beneath the desert surface!
A large shelled tortoise plods through the sand, looking for water.
A red and orange fish bubbles about in the water here.
A long yellow fish darts through the currents here.
A tiny turtle smiles and swims here.
A bright red fish swims slowly through the water here.
A gray-furred chimp hangs from a tree here.
A strange spined warthog charges about through the brush.
An odd striped anaconda hangs from a tree here.
A huge ape with stark white-yellow hair plods about the area here.
A bright red crab shuffles through the sand.
A dark blue crab waves his pincers menacingly at you!
A large, multicolored bird spreads its wings and takes to the sky.
A haggard man ambles through the sand, shielding himself from sunlight.
Mobiles.Description: There is not much you can see about this man through his many headwraps andrags.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A short bird with a slightly hooked beak stands on a branch here.
A man rolls over in the sand, attempting to draw you closer.
Mobiles.Description: Bearded and dirty, this desert dweller preys on hapless adventurers thatwould attempt to attack him while down.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A blur of sand whirls around here, then seems to die off.
A desperate nomad, outcast from the nomad clans, skulks about here.
Mobiles.Description: Ragged and filthy, this man bears the mark of a nomad outcast, not onlyin the vivid brand upon his forehead, poorly hidden by his greasy hair, butin the desperation and lonely hate in his eyes.  He clutches a sharp saber,and clearly intends to treat others as he feels he has been mistreated.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A bird with markings the color of sand hunts for food here.
`eIn a colorful flash of `borange`e scales, a fish evades a predator.``
`aAn oval fish with lots of teeth hunts for prey here.``
A maiden skillfully fishes here, clad only in the briefest of garments.
Mobiles.Description: Dark-eyed and haired, this slender maiden has left the comforts of thecity to better serve goals only she is sure of.  Based on the patterns shehas painted on herself, she felt a religious pull to abandon her formerlife.  She wields a fishing spear with apparent ease and a great deal ofgrace.

Mobiles.LongDescription: A piebald stallion races the wind.
Mobiles.Description: What a beautiful animal!  A long mane tosses in the wind as this spiritedbeast tries to outrace the wind and almost succeeds!

Mobiles.LongDescription: `eA graceful mare keeps pace with the herd stallion.
Mobiles.Description: With a delicacy of a true artist, this lovely mare ducks her head andfollows the herd stallion in a series of dancing steps.

Rooms.RoomDescription: Large, waxlike leaves that drooped low with clinging perspiration snap,almost springlike, back to their original position as you brush by them.The constant drip of water from the canopy adds an infrequent note tothe cacophony of sounds and voices that ring out periodically.  The pungentodor of broken plantlife hangs heavy in the humid air, clinging to yourclothes and armor as you pass.

Exotic flora forms a virtual wall around you as you make your way carefullythrough the thick tangle of vinery and plants.  Creatures of all typesscatter through the tropical evergreens as you stumble through the thickcongealing organic barriers.  Looking around, you are greeted with curiosof all sorts, ranging from brightly-colored birds to strange littleamphibians that fade into their backdrop.

No shadows manage to escape the relentless sun, only the blazingglare of light reflected off countless grains reaches the eye. Intensewaves of heat rise from below, distorting and blurring the sloping hillsand rolling valleys of shifting sand. The ground itself is constantly inmotion, footsteps falling on unstable ground, a tiny avalanche slidingaway with each, light breezes carrying fine sheets of sand across thedunes - only the occasional cactus or desert flower holds steady in theconstant motion.

The desert sands surround you, desolate and burning with light and heat.A few cacti manage to cling to life and grow here, producing large fleshyorange blossoms amidst the long spines. Some small birds perch atop thecacti, looking about for insects to provide them with food. Off in thedistance, through waves of heat, you can almost make out a clump of treessurrounding an oasis.

Trudging steadily through this desiccated wasteland of sand, you turn tolook around for any avenue of escape and find none.  Wizened cactiprovide a brief prophetic glimpse of exactly what your further journeyinginto this desert will be like.  Arid winds remove moisture from yourface as you turn to face the remaining expanses of parched land.

Tropical vegetation surrounds you closely in every direction, evokingslight, but previously dormant feelings of claustrophobia.  Huge, majesticsnakes curl down tree branches overhead and prepare to snap at their prey,possibly you.  In an attempt to nimbly avoid them, you find yourselfstruggling to free your feet from a morass of sand and vine growth thatwrap around your feet.

Reclusive predators snarl quietly from behind the cloak of tropical shadowsthat cover this area as you pass them.  The wailing cry of a downed animalquickly draws their attention elsewhere, leaving you to face this tangleof plants without having to deal with their intervention.  Fernlike leavesspiral downward to interlock with vines that seem to tie onto roots andfallen tree branches, making it quite a task to move anywhere.

Strange splintered cries of jungle predators cause you to move with an almostintense trepidation, throwing yourself against the near-impenetrable barrierof thick-leafed plants that block your way.  Hardened and exposed tree rootsact as anchors to ground and sky vines, forming a three dimensional net thattakes several skillful attempts to bypass.  Leaning against a spongy tree,you take a moment's rest from the torturous exercise of movement beforecontinuing your journey.

Currents wash over jagged red rocks and through loose piles of sand, siftingthe briny water and sending it to the river beyond.  Piles of pumice andsandstone act as natural sluices, catching and holding salt until animalscome to lick it away.  Far off in the distance you can see waves crashingagainst the remote shoals of this continent, far out on a shallow plateauof sand.

Rooms.RoomDescription: A spray of water lightly coats your face as large ocean waves towerupwards and come crashing down on the surface of the beach, sending turtlesand crabs plodding away for cover.  Beach grass and sea plants tanglemessily at the water's edge, forming a small organic reef that reaches intothe blue-green fluid, housing several colorful fish and animals.
